(42, 16, 3, 20, 18, 9, 9, 'I cannot dig; to beg I am ashamed', 'Connection of Stewardship and Slothfulness', 'This connection highlights the consequences of poor stewardship and laziness. The steward''s shame in not wanting to beg reflects a failure in responsibility, paralleling the idea that slothfulness in work leads to wastefulness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 3, 23, 10, 3, 3, NULL, 'Desperation and Seeking Help', 'This connection highlights a theme of desperation in both passages. The steward''s shame in seeking help parallels the inquiry in Isaiah about where to flee for assistance in times of trouble.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 3, 24, 5, 31, 31, 'my lord taketh away from me the stewardship', 'Stewardship and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in both passages. The steward''s concern about losing his position reflects a broader issue of leadership and responsibility, similar to the false prophets and priests in Jeremiah who mislead the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 3, 28, 9, 5, 5, NULL, 'Day of Reckoning Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in both passages. The steward''s concern about his future reflects a sense of urgency similar to the question posed in Hosea about what one will do in a solemn day.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 3, 41, 10, 46, 46, 'to beg I am ashamed', 'Connection of Stewardship and Begging', 'This connection highlights the theme of desperation in both passages. The steward''s shame in begging parallels Bartimeus''s position as a beggar, emphasizing their social vulnerability.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 4, 20, 30, 9, 9, 'receive me into their houses', 'Stewardship and Dependence on God', 'This connection highlights the theme of reliance on others and the consequences of one''s actions. Both passages emphasize the importance of not becoming overly self-sufficient or desperate, which can lead to denying God or acting immorally.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 4, 24, 4, 22, 22, NULL, 'Foolishness and Preparation', 'This connection highlights the theme of preparation for future consequences. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the lack of understanding and wisdom, with the steward in Luke seeking to secure his future while the people in Jeremiah are described as foolish and lacking knowledge.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 4, 59, 3, 15, 15, NULL, 'Wisdom and Earthly Actions', 'This connection highlights the contrast between earthly wisdom and the shrewdness of the steward. Both passages emphasize actions driven by self-interest rather than divine guidance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 5, 42, 7, 41, 42, 'How much owest thou unto my lord?', 'Debt and Forgiveness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of debt and the act of forgiveness. In Luke 16:5, the focus is on the debtors of a lord, while Luke 7:41-42 illustrates forgiveness of debts, prompting reflection on love in response to forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 5, 40, 18, 24, 24, 'How much owest thou unto my lord?', 'Debt and Reckoning Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of debt and the process of reckoning with those who owe. In Luke, the steward addresses debtors, while in Matthew, a servant is brought before a master to settle a significant debt.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 6, 42, 16, 12, 12, NULL, 'Faithfulness and Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the theme of faithfulness in stewardship. The first passage illustrates a servant''s management of another''s resources, while the second emphasizes the importance of being faithful in what belongs to others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 6, 56, 2, 10, 10, NULL, 'Faithfulness in Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the theme of fidelity in stewardship. In Luke, the steward reduces debts, demonstrating a form of good management, while Titus emphasizes showing good fidelity in all things, aligning with responsible conduct.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 6, 42, 16, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Financial Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the theme of managing resources wisely. In both passages, there is an emphasis on using material wealth (''mammon of unrighteousness'') to create lasting relationships and secure a future.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 7, 22, 8, 11, 12, NULL, 'Financial Transactions in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of financial dealings and the management of resources. Both passages involve the concept of debts and payments, illustrating the responsibilities associated with stewardship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 7, 42, 20, 9, 9, NULL, 'Parables of Stewardship', 'Both passages emphasize the management of resources and responsibilities. The steward in Luke 16:7 adjusts debts, while the vineyard owner in Luke 20:9 entrusts his vineyard to husbandmen, highlighting themes of accountability and stewardship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 7, 42, 20, 12, 12, NULL, 'Theme of Debt and Rejection', 'This connection highlights the theme of financial obligation and rejection. In both passages, there is a sense of dealing with debts and the consequences of failing to meet them.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 8, 52, 5, 5, 5, 'children of this world', 'Children of Light Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between ''children of this world'' and ''children of light.'' Both passages emphasize the distinction between those who operate in wisdom and those who live in darkness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 8, 49, 5, 8, 8, 'children of light', 'Wisdom of Light vs. Darkness', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the ''children of this world'' and the ''children of light.'' Both passages emphasize the importance of wisdom and behavior in relation to one''s spiritual state.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 8, 20, 6, 6, 8, 'wiser than the children of light', 'Wisdom in Preparation', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom in preparation and resourcefulness. Both passages emphasize the importance of being proactive and wise in managing resources, as seen in the steward''s actions and the ant''s diligence.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 8, 42, 16, 10, 10, 'wiser than the children of light', 'Faithfulness and Wisdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of faithfulness in small matters as a reflection of one''s character in larger issues. The unjust steward''s wise actions demonstrate a shrewdness that contrasts with the faithfulness expected from the children of light.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 8, 43, 12, 36, 36, 'children of light', 'Wisdom of the Children of Light', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the ''children of this world'' and the ''children of light.'' Both passages emphasize the importance of wisdom and belief in the light, suggesting a call to recognize and act upon spiritual insight.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 16, 8, 1, 3, 1, 1, 'wiser than the children of light', 'Wisdom and Cunning in Context', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom and cunning in both passages. The ''children of this world'' in Luke reflect the ''subtil'' nature of the serpent in Genesis, suggesting a shared understanding of shrewdness in navigating their respective environments.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
